354
00:30:41,673 --> 00:30:53,359
[SPEAKER_00]: I just wanted to say, if I understood the intent of your work, Milva, correctly, and thank you for doing that, I actually think it's exactly what I would suggest that we do, because we do have a big task.

355
00:30:53,379 --> 00:31:04,904
[SPEAKER_00]: A charter is 10 articles, but if we break it down, mayor or city manager, if we want, legislative, school committee, budget process, et cetera, it's gonna move.

356
00:31:05,185 --> 00:31:06,305
[SPEAKER_00]: We do it a chunk at a time.

357
00:31:07,105 --> 00:31:09,927
[SPEAKER_00]: And I think having subcommittees focused on those

358
00:31:11,012 --> 00:31:25,285
[SPEAKER_00]: and then developing a draft for the whole committee to review, provide substantive input with larger context from the subcommittee, from our outside help, I think is the best way to actually, to wrestle with the complexity here.

359
00:31:25,585 --> 00:31:34,454
[SPEAKER_00]: I think we need something to react against in order to come up with how we want the city council to work, how we want the executive to relate to it and so on.

360
00:31:35,381 --> 00:31:44,243
[SPEAKER_00]: Um, and I think public input is really important and everyone's touched on that, but I think having the public react to something really makes it useful.

361
00:31:44,483 --> 00:31:51,825
[SPEAKER_00]: You know, uh, to a certain point, asking general abstract questions, um, isn't going to give us a lot.

362
00:31:51,885 --> 00:31:53,245
[SPEAKER_00]: I think we have to give them something.

363
00:31:53,465 --> 00:32:03,087
[SPEAKER_00]: So I think if we could come up with draft city council and discuss it internally, and then that's subject to a hearing of its own potentially.

364
00:32:03,984 --> 00:32:11,387
[SPEAKER_00]: or some other opportunity for impact, I think would go a lot further than just sort of asking the public what it thinks.

365
00:32:12,248 --> 00:32:16,109
[SPEAKER_00]: So if, again, if I understood you correctly, I think that's exactly what we should do.

366
00:32:17,710 --> 00:32:18,410
[SPEAKER_12]: Thank you, John.

367
00:32:19,291 --> 00:32:28,955
[SPEAKER_12]: So I just wanna just to summarize kind of what the vision is or what my vision was when I made the work plan.

368
00:32:30,227 --> 00:32:33,929
[SPEAKER_12]: just want to point out, if we were an elected commission, we would have 18 months.

369
00:32:35,530 --> 00:32:39,833
